    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram in cipher—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Choate states that the American owners of cargo in the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Mashona</hi> should prove their damages, if any, in prize court.]</p>
            </div>
